16/08/2010
BERLIN, Germany -- Police arrested a Croatian citizen wanted in Bulgaria for drug trafficking on Saturday (August 14th).
The 39-year old Croat, whose name was not released, was detained based on an international arrest warrant upon his arrival in Dortmund from the Croatian town of Split.
Juergen Karlisch, spokesman for the Dortmund police, told HINA news agency that Bulgaria had sentenced the man to seven and a half years in prison for drug trafficking.
(HINA, Nova TV, HRT - 15/08/10)
